reviews.summary:
This work trains reasoning-capable LLMs from expert demonstrations without task-specific verifiers. It frames learning as adversarial inverse RL: a shared LLM plays both a policy that generates CoT answers and a relativistic critic that compares (expert, policy) answer pairs to provide a learned reward, optimized via KL-regularized GRPO.

Contributions: 
1. a demonstration-only, verifier-free IRL formulation for reasoning training; 
2. a relativistic pairwise critic with tie rewards to stabilize learning; 
3. strong empirical gains across verifiable and non-verifiable tasks.
